	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				there is so much good and bad information on all of these item &quot;info&quot; pages. . . .  <BR>
<BR>
about the camp - it's pretty much been said already, so i'll just confirm that this is a looooooooooooooooooong camp.  if you got a sash in 5 hours, as someone above said, then you are very lucky.  that is certainly not the average time.  i play on Cazic-Thule server and have camped this thing for 16 hours straight and seen no sashes, and again 12 hours straight and seen no sashes.  Then again, i've heard of 4 sashes dropping in 5 hours before - it's completely random, just rare drop off a rare as heck spawn.  the way it's done on my server is usually by list.  that is, group that takes room randoms for spot on list from one to 6, then new members are added at bottom of list when someone leaves.  this is a little fairer to the poor ba$tard who just sat there for 20 hours waiting for a sash than randoming it would be.<BR>
<BR>
level to camp it - 45+ is nicer, but you should be 40+ at least to really contribute anything to the group camping this room, IMO.<BR>
<BR>
price - the guy who says he's on Cazic-Thule and can buy these for 1k plat is lying.  i play on CT and these go for a couple k pp more than smr, which now sells for 10-12k pp.  prices are falling since kunark, but nobody has ever sold this for 1000pp unless they didn't know what they were doing.  this remains an extremely valuable item on an old server (like CT) because the rarity of the drop makes it still desirable as more and more people get to the level where they can conceivably camp it.  i know several high level (49+ on up into low 50's) meleers who still don't have a sash (and who bug me about getting them one, as i can be found camping this a lot lately), so it's not the ubiquitous item among high-levels that you might think it would be.<BR>
<BR>
i'll reiterate - this can be a looooooooooong camp.  the frenzy spawns very rarely, and he always seems to have that stupid ring, so be prepared for some frustration if you think you are going to get in the frenzy group and walk out with a sash a couple hours later.  i have left the camp twice now when i was 1st on the list for a sash (and have seen others do the same) because i just couldn't keep my eyes open.  not a camp for the &quot;casual gamer&quot; who likes to just come and play a couple hours now and then; you have to be ready to really dig in and camp this thing for a long time if you want a reasonable chance at it.<BR>
<BR>
course you could get lucky and get one in an hour or two too - just odds are you won't. =)<BR>
<BR>
anyway - cheers to all the frenzy campers!  you're a bunch of diehards and i envy your persistence when i collapse from exhaustion after 16 hours. =)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
